	<Title>
		Quit smoking: Don&apos;t give up
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Quitting smoking may be one of the hardest challenges you&apos;ll face. For most people, it takes several tries to overcome tobacco dependence. If you&apos;ve tried to quit smoking before but took it up again, think about what struggles you faced and why you started again. What helped you stop cravings and what didn&apos;t? What made you pick up that first cigarette after you&apos;d quit? If you didn&apos;t use stop-smoking products last time, consider them this time. Or counseling. Keep a journal about quitting. Think what else you can do differently this time to quit smoking for good.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
